special topics in group theory page 1 department colloquium thursday january 19 4 15pm building 380 room 380 w zhiwei yun mit motives and the inverse galois problem abstract we will use geometric langlands theory to solve two problems concerning number fields one is serre's question of whether there exist motives over q with motivic galois group of type e8 or g2 we will explain what this means and why it is interesting the other is the concrete question of whether there are galois extensions of q with galois group equal to e8 p or g2 p the finite simple groups of lie type the answers to both questions are yes
